<font size="2"><b>Proud leader of The Forgotten Truth in DAoC
<font size="1"><b><i>"Wait!  I'm lost!"</i></b></font> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucreepypete.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CreepyPete</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/15/02 10:55:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1046.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tuesday Night Dartmoor Hunt</span><hr size=1> Hunting DM can be very frustrating and challenging. It's very easy to get an overwhelming number of adds if you're not careful (and sometimes even if you are), as evidenced by the death spam you see if you're hunting in Cornwall. You need an extremely powerful group that is used to working together to stand much of a chance unless you stay in the pony area. Here's some hints that I've learned from Boldwin and co.:<br>
<br>
1) Dont autofollow on the wall. Can pick up weird agro.<br>
<br>
2) Cloth casters and anyone who doesnt want to get beat on need to stay close to the cleric. When multiples come in they need to be close to the cleric that will be stunning them. If they're agro on you 25 yds behind the party you can kiss the bindstone for better luck next time.<br>
<br>
3) Don't be mad if you die. You're going to die a LOT.<br>
<br>
