I will try to be on to help out if I can. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ushadowmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowmage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/16/02 7:01:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1046.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tuesday Night Dartmoor Hunt</span><hr size=1> Here is a Baf Df code hint I found out. If you help some one kill a baf mob and you then attack another baf mob the code thinks thay you and the person/group you helped is part of your group.  I.E. a group of 8 gets 4 bafs another group of 8 yells for help and you attack their mob. You now go back to pull your baf mob the code now thinks you have 16 meabers in your group and will send 8+ mobs becuase it thinks there is 16 of you not 8. to clear this attack a non baf or every one need to log. <p>Renshai NightSlayer 
